<TITLE> Hasina condoles families of officers killed in chopper crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 11 (bdnews24.com) Prime minister Sheikh Hasina Wednesday expressed condolences to the families of the two army officers killed in a helicopter crash on Monday. Maj Gen Rafiqul Islam, general officer commanding of Jessore-based 55 Infantry Division, and pilot Lt Col Shahidul Islam were killed when their helicopter went down in Kalihati, Tangail, after hitting power lines. Hasina went to the Combined Military Hospital at around 9am to see the families who were paying their last respects to the two dead officers. The government announced that the nation would observe Wednesday as a mourning day for the two army officers. National flags were flying at half-mast across the country and at Bangladesh missions abroad. Their namaj-e-janaza was held at 4pm at the Army Stadium in Dhaka, alongside Col Gulzar Uddin Ahmed and Lt Col Manzur-e-Elahi Chowdhury, who were killed in the BDR mutiny last month The bodies of Col Gulzar Uddin Ahmed and Lt Col Manzur-e-Elahi were identified Tuesday, almost two weeks after their deaths, through forensic tests. bdnew
